CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 6, 1941, pg. 2 reads: "Prattis Asks About The Navy Problem - P.L. Prattis, executive editor of The Courier (extreme right) and Mrs. Roosevelt, at the Flyers' Club, County Airport, Thursday. Mr. Prattis questioned the First Lady on the Negro and the Navy. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Men and women greeting Eleanor Roosevelt at Allegheny County Airport, with mounted police in background
